President Biden is set to virtually meet with G7 leaders on August 24, 2021. The main topics of discussion will be the ongoing coordination of Afghanistan policy, the evacuation of citizens, Afghan allies, and other vulnerable individuals. Additionally, plans for providing humanitarian aid and support for Afghan refugees will be addressed. This meeting follows President Biden's recent phone calls with G7 leaders including Prime Minister Boris Johnson, Chancellor Angela Merkel, President Emmanuel Macron, and Prime Minister Mario Draghi.